# Chainlink Oracle Data

## Purpose

Automated script to fetch and optimize Chainlink oracle data from official APIs, generating clean JSON files with only essential fields needed by the frontend.

## Usage

To update oracle data files:

```bash
pnpm generate:chainlink
```

This fetches fresh data from all networks and generates optimized JSON files in this directory.

## Adding New Networks

To add support for a new network, update the `ENDPOINTS` object in `scripts/generate-chainlink-data.ts`:

```typescript
const ENDPOINTS = {
  mainnet: 'https://reference-data-directory.vercel.app/feeds-mainnet.json',
  base: 'https://reference-data-directory.vercel.app/feeds-ethereum-mainnet-base-1.json',
  polygon: 'https://reference-data-directory.vercel.app/feeds-polygon-mainnet-katana.json',
  arbitrum: 'https://reference-data-directory.vercel.app/feeds-ethereum-mainnet-arbitrum-1.json',
  // Add new network here
};
```

## API Reference

Official Chainlink data feed APIs:

- **Mainnet**: https://reference-data-directory.vercel.app/feeds-mainnet.json
- **Base**: https://reference-data-directory.vercel.app/feeds-ethereum-mainnet-base-1.json
- **Polygon**: https://reference-data-directory.vercel.app/feeds-polygon-mainnet-katana.json
- **Optimism**: https://reference-data-directory.vercel.app/feeds-ethereum-mainnet-optimism-1.json
- **Arbitrum**: https://reference-data-directory.vercel.app/feeds-ethereum-mainnet-arbitrum-1.json

Source: [Chainlink Documentation](https://docs.chain.link/data-feeds/price-feeds/addresses)
